From 3b2966e72c414592cd2c86c21a0d4664cf627b9c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Roger Pau Monne <roger.pau@citrix.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Nov 2017 12:52:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] libevtchn: fix build on non-Linux hosts
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Non-Linux hosts (where osdep_evtchn_restrict is not yet supported)
made use of errno without including errno.h, fix this by including the
header.

Signed-off-by: Roger Pau Monn√© <roger.pau@citrix.com>
Acked-by: Wei Liu <wei.liu2@citrix.com>
Release-acked-by: Julien Grall <julien.grall@linaro.org>
diff --git a/tools/libs/evtchn/freebsd.c b/tools/libs/evtchn/freebsd.c
index ba82f06..6564ed4 100644
--- a/tools/libs/evtchn/freebsd.c
+++ b/tools/libs/evtchn/freebsd.c
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
  * Split off from xc_freebsd_osdep.c
  */
 
+#include <errno.h>
 #include <fcntl.h>
 #include <unistd.h>
 
